rs. Policy makers, donor governments and humanitarian organizations, especially those adopting a "rights-based" approach, will also find it an invaluable resource. But it is the refugees themselves who could benefit the most if these actors absorb its lessons and apply them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aRefugeesxLegal status, laws, etc.zAfrica, Eastern. 0aRefugeeszAfrica, Eastern. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh1 aAlbie Sachs, Justice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarrell-Bond, Barbara, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781782387268?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782387268423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782387268/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK